eriRouterIpPoolMib.name: eriRouterIpPoolMib

revisions.description: Updated RBN/rbn/Rbn as ERICSSON-ROUTER/eriRouter/EriRouter to migrate RBN MIB to ERICSSON MIB.

Defined textual conventions for representing IP Pool type and threshold management: EriRouterInetPoolType, EriRouterInetIpPoolThresholdType, EriRouterInetIpPoolThreshold, and EriRouterInetIpPoolThrshNotify. Added the following tables and notifications to support IPv6: eriRouterInetIpPoolTable, eriRouterInetIpPoolCtxTable, eriRouterInetIpPoolHiFallingThrshMet, eriRouterInetIpPoolLoFallingThrshMet, eriRouterInetIpPoolCtxHiFallingThrshMet, eriRouterInetIpPoolCtxLoFallingThrshMet, Updated CONTACT-INFO.
Added an IP Pool total size object, an IP Pool percentage threshold table and a notification for monitoring per-context IP Pool percentage thresholds.
Added an ip pool type, an end ip address for range ip pools, and updated conformance information.
Added an ip pool name and updated conformance information.

eriRouterIpPoolMib.description: Defines the objects necessary to obtain information about IP Pools for interfaces within a context.

EriRouterInetPoolType.name: EriRouterInetPoolType
EriRouterInetPoolType.description: Denotes a generic IP Pool Type.

EriRouterInetIpPoolThresholdType.name: EriRouterInetIpPoolThresholdType
EriRouterInetIpPoolThresholdType.description: A value that represents a type of IP Pool threshold value. none(0) No threshold setting. This value MUST be used if the value of all corresponding EriRouterInetIpPoolThreshold objects in the same logical row are zeroes. absolute(1) EriRouterInetIpPoolThreshold values in the same logical row defined as absolute values with the range of (1..IP Pool size) percentage(2) EriRouterInetIpPoolThreshold values in the same logical row defined as percentages with the range of (1..100). Implementations must ensure that EriRouterInetIpPoolThresholdType objects and any dependent objects (e.g., EriRouterInetIpPoolThreshold objects) are consistent. The relationship between absolute value and percentage is: absolute = IP Pool size * percentage

EriRouterInetIpPoolThreshold.name: EriRouterInetIpPoolThreshold
EriRouterInetIpPoolThreshold.description: Denotes a generic IP Pool threshold. An EriRouterInetIpPoolThreshold value is always interpreted within the context of an EriRouterInetIpPoolThresholdType value. The usages of the EriRouterInetIpPoolThreshold textual convention in the same logical row is required to specify the EriRouterInetIpPoolThresholdType object that provides the context. The value of an EriRouterInetIpPoolThreshold object must always be consistent with the value of the associated EriRouterInetIpPoolThresholdType object.

EriRouterInetIpPoolThrshNotify.name: EriRouterInetIpPoolThrshNotify
EriRouterInetIpPoolThrshNotify.description: Denotes a logging method for monitoring falling thresholds

eriRouterIpPoolTable.name: eriRouterIpPoolTable
eriRouterIpPoolTable.description: The purpose of this table is to allow customers to monitor the status of IP Pools on their SMS systems through SNMP. This table contains the objects which identify information about IP Pools. Each row in the table corresponds to one IP Pool for a given interface within a particular context. Objects defined in this table are only accessible within the context identified in the SNMP protocol (i.e. the community string in v1/v2c or the contextName in v3).

eriRouterIpPoolEntry.name: eriRouterIpPoolEntry
eriRouterIpPoolEntry.description: A conceptual row in the eriRouterIpPoolTable.

eriRouterIpPoolInterfaceIdx.name: eriRouterIpPoolInterfaceIdx
eriRouterIpPoolInterfaceIdx.description: The index of the interface containing the IP Pool.

eriRouterIpPoolAddr.name: eriRouterIpPoolAddr
eriRouterIpPoolAddr.description: The start address of the IP Pool.

eriRouterIpPoolInterfaceName.name: eriRouterIpPoolInterfaceName
eriRouterIpPoolInterfaceName.description: The name of the interface containing the IP Pool.

eriRouterIpPoolMask.name: eriRouterIpPoolMask
eriRouterIpPoolMask.description: The subnet mask of the IP Pool. This object will be instantiated for IP Pools of type subnet only.

eriRouterIpPoolSize.name: eriRouterIpPoolSize
eriRouterIpPoolSize.description: The size of the IP Pool is defined to be the sum of the available addresses plus the unusable addresses.

eriRouterIpPoolAvailable.name: eriRouterIpPoolAvailable
eriRouterIpPoolAvailable.description: The number of addresses of an IP Pool that are available.

eriRouterIpPoolUnusable.name: eriRouterIpPoolUnusable
eriRouterIpPoolUnusable.description: Unusable IP addresses in an IP Pool consist of the ip address of the interface, and those used by the network address and the broadcast address of the interface.

eriRouterIpPoolInuse.name: eriRouterIpPoolInuse
eriRouterIpPoolInuse.description: The number of addresses of an IP Pool that are in use.

eriRouterIpPoolThreshold.name: eriRouterIpPoolThreshold
eriRouterIpPoolThreshold.description: The threshold of an IP Pool is the value for currently available addresses, as reported in eriRouterIpPoolAvailable, which causes a trap and/or log message to be generated when this value is reached. This is a falling threshold, so a trap and/or log message will only be sent on a transition of the value of available addresss from (eriRouterIpPoolThreshold+1) addresses to eriRouterIpPoolThreshold addresses. Additionally, the action of sending the trap and/or log message is subject to the values of eriRouterIpPoolSendTrap and eriRouterIpPoolLogMessage. A value of zero means there is no threshold.

eriRouterIpPoolSendTrap.name: eriRouterIpPoolSendTrap
eriRouterIpPoolSendTrap.description: If true, upon detection of reaching a per-pool threshold event, a trap will be sent. See the definition of the eriRouterIpPoolThresholdMet for the information included in the trap. Note, both eriRouterIpPoolSendTrap and eriRouterIpPoolLogMessage are allowed to be TRUE at the same time.

eriRouterIpPoolLogMessage.name: eriRouterIpPoolLogMessage
eriRouterIpPoolLogMessage.description: If true, upon detection of reaching a per-pool threshold event, a message will be logged. The information contained in the message is the same as that included in the eriRouterIpPoolThresholdMet trap. Note, both eriRouterIpPoolSendTrap and eriRouterIpPoolLogMessage are allowed to be TRUE at the same time.

eriRouterIpPoolName.name: eriRouterIpPoolName
eriRouterIpPoolName.description: The name of the IP Pool.

eriRouterIpPoolType.name: eriRouterIpPoolType
eriRouterIpPoolType.description: The type of the IP Pool.

eriRouterIpPoolEndAddr.name: eriRouterIpPoolEndAddr
eriRouterIpPoolEndAddr.description: The end address of the IP Pool. This object will be instantiated for range IP Pools only.

eriRouterIpPoolContextName.name: eriRouterIpPoolContextName
eriRouterIpPoolContextName.description: The name of the context containing the IP Pool.

eriRouterIpPoolContextAvailable.name: eriRouterIpPoolContextAvailable
eriRouterIpPoolContextAvailable.description: The total number of IP addresses available in all pools of all interfaces in the context valid in the current view.

eriRouterIpPoolContextThreshold.name: eriRouterIpPoolContextThreshold
eriRouterIpPoolContextThreshold.description: The per-context threshold of an IP Pool is the value for currently available per-context addresses, as reported in eriRouterIpPoolContextAvailable, which causes a trap and/or log message to be generated when this value is reached. This is a falling threshold, so a trap and/or log message will only be sent on a transition of the value of available addresss from (eriRouterIpPoolContextThreshold+1) addresses to eriRouterIpPoolContextThreshold addresses. Additionally, the action of sending the trap and/or log message is subject to the values of eriRouterIpPoolContextSendTrap and eriRouterIpPoolContextLogMessage. A value of zero means there is no per-context threshold.

eriRouterIpPoolContextSendTrap.name: eriRouterIpPoolContextSendTrap
eriRouterIpPoolContextSendTrap.description: If true, upon detection of a per-context threshold crossing event, a trap will be sent. See the definition of the eriRouterIpPoolContextThresholdMet for the information included in the trap. Note, both eriRouterIpPoolContextSendTrap and eriRouterIpPoolContextLogMessage are allowed to be true at the same time.

eriRouterIpPoolContextLogMessage.name: eriRouterIpPoolContextLogMessage
eriRouterIpPoolContextLogMessage.description: If true, upon detection of a per-context threshold crossing event, a message will be logged. The information contained in the message logged is the same as that included in the eriRouterIpPoolContextThresholdMet trap. Note, both eriRouterIpPoolContextSendTrap and eriRouterIpPoolContextLogMessage are allowed to be true at the same time.

eriRouterIpPoolContextTotalSize.name: eriRouterIpPoolContextTotalSize
eriRouterIpPoolContextTotalSize.description: The total number of IP addresses configured in all pools of all interfaces in the context valid in the current view. It is the sum of the available addresses plus the unusable addresses.

eriRouterIpPoolContextThresholdPercentTa.name: eriRouterIpPoolContextThresholdPercentTable
eriRouterIpPoolContextThresholdPercentTa.description: The purpose of this table is to allow customers to monitor the status of per-context IP Pool percentage thresholds through SNMP. This table contains the objects which identify information about per-context IP Pool thresholds expressed in percentage. Each row in the table corresponds to one IP Pool percentage threshold configured within a particular context. Objects defined in this table are only accessible within the context identified in the SNMP protocol (i.e. the community string in v1/v2c or the contextName in v3).

eriRouterIpPoolContextThresholdIndex.name: eriRouterIpPoolContextThresholdIndex
eriRouterIpPoolContextThresholdIndex.description: The index of the IP Pool percentage threshold.

eriRouterIpPoolContextThresholdPercentag.name: eriRouterIpPoolContextThresholdPercentage
eriRouterIpPoolContextThresholdPercentag.description: A threshold for the percentage of the number of currently available IP Pool addresses against the total number of IP Pool addresses configured within the context. This is a falling threshold, so an SNMP trap and/or log message will only be sent when the current value, which is the % of eriRouterIpPoolContextAvailable/eriRouterIpPoolContextTotalSize truncated to a whole number in percentage, is less than or equal to this threshold, and the percentage value at the last check was greater than this threshold. Additionally, the action of sending the SNMP trap and/or logging a message is subject to the values of eriRouterIpPoolContextThresholdSendTrap and eriRouterIpPoolContextThresholdLogMessage.

eriRouterIpPoolContextThresholdSendTrap.name: eriRouterIpPoolContextThresholdSendTrap
eriRouterIpPoolContextThresholdSendTrap.description: If true, upon detection of a per-context threshold crossing event, an SNMP trap will be sent. See the definition of the eriRouterIpPoolContextThresholdPercentageMet for the information included in the trap. Note, both eriRouterIpPoolContextThresholdSendTrap and eriRouterIpPoolContextThresholdLogMessage are allowed to be true at the same time.

eriRouterIpPoolContextThresholdLogMessag.name: eriRouterIpPoolContextThresholdLogMessage
eriRouterIpPoolContextThresholdLogMessag.description: If true, upon detection of a per-context threshold crossing event, a message will be logged. The information contained in the message logged is the same as that included in the eriRouterIpPoolContextThresholdPercentageMet trap. Note, both eriRouterIpPoolContextThresholdSendTrap and eriRouterIpPoolContextThresholdLogMessage are allowed to be true at the same time.

eriRouterIpPoolThresholdMet.name: eriRouterIpPoolThresholdMet
eriRouterIpPoolThresholdMet.description: A notification indicating that the per pool falling threshold has been reached.

eriRouterIpPoolContextThresholdMet.name: eriRouterIpPoolContextThresholdMet
eriRouterIpPoolContextThresholdMet.description: A notification indicating that the per-context falling threshold has been reached.

eriRouterIpPoolContextThresholdPercentag.name: eriRouterIpPoolContextThresholdPercentageMet
eriRouterIpPoolContextThresholdPercentag.description: A notification indicating that the per-context percentage falling threshold has been reached.

eriRouterInetIpPoolTable.name: eriRouterInetIpPoolTable
eriRouterInetIpPoolTable.description: This table contains the objects which identify information about IP Pools (such as ND IPv6 pool and DHCP-PD IPv6 Pool). Each row in the table corresponds to one IP Pool for either a given interface within a particular context or only within a particular context . If this pool is only configured per context basis, the interface index is set to zero. The IPv6 pool range is from start prefix/length to the end prefix/length. The prefix length for start and end prefixes are the same, and refer to the prefix length to be advertised or delegated. Objects defined in this table are only accessible within the context identified in the SNMP protocol (i.e. the community string in v1/v2c or the contextName in v3).

eriRouterInetIpPoolEntry.name: eriRouterInetIpPoolEntry
eriRouterInetIpPoolEntry.description: A conceptual row in the eriRouterInetIpPoolTable.

eriRouterInetIpPoolIfIndex.name: eriRouterInetIpPoolIfIndex
eriRouterInetIpPoolIfIndex.description: The index of the interface containing the IP Pool. The interface identified by a particular value of this index is the same interface as identified by the same value of the IF-MIB's ifIndex.

eriRouterInetIpPoolStartPrefix.name: eriRouterInetIpPoolStartPrefix
eriRouterInetIpPoolStartPrefix.description: The start address prefix of this pool. The address type of this object is specified in eriRouterInetIpPoolPrefixType. The length of this object is the standard length for objects of that type (always 16 bytes). Any bits after eriRouterInetIpPoolStartPrefixLen must be zero.

eriRouterInetIpPoolStartPrefixLen.name: eriRouterInetIpPoolStartPrefixLen
eriRouterInetIpPoolStartPrefixLen.description: The prefix length associated with this prefix. It refers to advertised or delegated prefix length.

eriRouterInetIpPoolEndPrefixType.name: eriRouterInetIpPoolEndPrefixType
eriRouterInetIpPoolEndPrefixType.description: The address type of eriRouterInetIpPoolPrefix. The value of this object is always ipv6 (2).

eriRouterInetIpPoolEndPrefix.name: eriRouterInetIpPoolEndPrefix
eriRouterInetIpPoolEndPrefix.description: The end IP address prefix of this pool. The address type of this object is specified in eriRouterInetIpPoolPrefixType. Any bits after eriRouterInetIpPoolPrefixLen must be zero.

eriRouterInetIpPoolEndPrefixLen.name: eriRouterInetIpPoolEndPrefixLen
eriRouterInetIpPoolEndPrefixLen.description: The IP prefix length associated with this prefix. It refers to the advertised or delegated prefix length. See eriRouterInetIpPoolEndPrefixLen.

eriRouterInetIpPoolInterfaceName.name: eriRouterInetIpPoolInterfaceName
eriRouterInetIpPoolInterfaceName.description: The name of the interface containing the IP Pool.

eriRouterInetIpPoolName.name: eriRouterInetIpPoolName
eriRouterInetIpPoolName.description: The name of the IP Pool.

eriRouterInetIpPoolSize.name: eriRouterInetIpPoolSize
eriRouterInetIpPoolSize.description: The size of the IP Pool is defined to be the sum of the available prefixes plus the unusable prefixes.

eriRouterInetIpPoolAvailable.name: eriRouterInetIpPoolAvailable
eriRouterInetIpPoolAvailable.description: The number of IP address prefixes of an IP Pool that are available.

eriRouterInetIpPoolUnusable.name: eriRouterInetIpPoolUnusable
eriRouterInetIpPoolUnusable.description: Unusable IP prefixes in an IP Pool.

eriRouterInetIpPoolInuse.name: eriRouterInetIpPoolInuse
eriRouterInetIpPoolInuse.description: The number of IP prefixes of an IP Pool that are in use.

eriRouterInetIpPoolThrshType.name: eriRouterInetIpPoolThrshType
eriRouterInetIpPoolThrshType.description: This object indicates the value type of all threshold values in this logical row, including eriRouterInetIpPoolHiFallingThrsh, eriRouterInetIpPoolLoFallingThrsh.

eriRouterInetIpPoolHiFallingThrsh.name: eriRouterInetIpPoolHiFallingThrsh
eriRouterInetIpPoolHiFallingThrsh.description: The falling threshold of an IP Pool. When the value of eriRouterInetIpPoolAvailable crosses from (eriRouterInetIpPoolHiFallingThrsh + 1) to eriRouterInetIpPoolHiFallingThrsh in either absolute value or percentage specified by eriRouterInetIpPoolThrshType, a eriRouterInetIpPoolHiFallingThrshMet notification and/or log is generated. The value of this object should never be smaller than the value of eriRouterInetIpPoolLoFallingThrsh. A value of zero means that this falling threshold is not configured.

eriRouterInetIpPoolHiFallingNotify.name: eriRouterInetIpPoolHiFallingNotify
eriRouterInetIpPoolHiFallingNotify.description: This object specifies if eriRouterInetIpPoolHiFallingThrshMet and/or log is generated. See the description of eriRouterInetIpPoolHiFallingThrsh for conditions which generate the notification.

eriRouterInetIpPoolLoFallingThrsh.name: eriRouterInetIpPoolLoFallingThrsh
eriRouterInetIpPoolLoFallingThrsh.description: The falling threshold of an IP Pool. When the value of eriRouterInetIpPoolAvailable crosses from (eriRouterInetIpPoolLoFallingThrsh + 1) to eriRouterInetIpPoolLoFallingThrsh (either absolute value or percentage) specified by eriRouterInetIpPoolThrshType, a eriRouterInetIpPoolLoFallingThrshMet notification and/or log is generated. The value of this object should never be greater than the value of eriRouterInetIpPoolHiFallingThrsh. A value of zero means that this falling threshold is not configured.

eriRouterInetIpPoolLoFallingNotify.name: eriRouterInetIpPoolLoFallingNotify
eriRouterInetIpPoolLoFallingNotify.description: This object specifies if eriRouterInetIpPoolLoFallingThrshMet and/or log is generated. See the description of eriRouterInetIpPoolLoFallingThrsh for conditions which generate the notification.

eriRouterInetIpPoolCtxName.name: eriRouterInetIpPoolCtxName
eriRouterInetIpPoolCtxName.description: The name of the context containing the IP Pool.

eriRouterInetIpPoolCtxTable.name: eriRouterInetIpPoolCtxTable
eriRouterInetIpPoolCtxTable.description: The purpose of this table is to allow customers to monitor the status of IP Pool context summary and thresholds through SNMP. This table contains the objects which identify information about per-context IP Pool thresholds expressed in absolute value or percentage. Each row in the table corresponds to one IP Pool threshold configured within a particular context. Objects defined in this table are only accessible within the context identified in the SNMP protocol (i.e. the community string in v1/v2c or the contextName in v3).
